clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: For the treatment of HIV 1 infection in combination with other antiretroviral agents

contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Amprenavir is a protease inhibitor with activity against Human Immunodeficiency Virus Type 1 HIV 1 Protease inhibitors block the part of HIV called protease HIV 1 protease is an enzyme required for the proteolytic cleavage of the viral polyprotein precursors into the individual functional proteins found in infectious HIV 1 Amprenavir binds to the protease active site and inhibits the activity of the enzyme This inhibition prevents cleavage of the viral polyproteins resulting in the formation of immature non infectious viral particles Protease inhibitors are almost always used in combination with at least two other anti HIV drugs
